'''Arthur Adams''' (born [[April 5]], [[1960s#1963|1963]]) is a [[Star Wars comic books|comic book]] illustrator who drew one of the covers for the ''[[Classic Star Wars: A New Hope]]'' series and contributed to the [[Star Wars Handbook 1: X-Wing Rogue Squadron|''Rogue Squadron'' handbook]] published by [[Dark Horse Comics]]. He started in the industry working for [[Marvel Comics]] on the mini-series titled ''Longshot'' published in [[1985]]. He worked on a number of titles for Marvel through the years and later created his own series called [[Wikipedia:Monkeyman and O'Brien|''Monkeyman and O'Brien'']] published by Dark Horse.

